.SH NAME
dots-add - Copy a file or directory into the active profile


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdots add [PATH] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Copy a file or directory from the home directory into the active profile and update the profile tracking database. PATH defaults to the current directory. Paths inside the configured dots repo are refused.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for add


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file path (overrides DOTS_CONFIG; default $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dots/config.toml or ~/.config/dots/config.toml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile name (overrides DOTS_PROFILE and config profile)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdots(1)\fP


